en_167468_1	The bill, which was signed in private at the White House, also imposes sanctions on Iran and North Korea.
en_167468_2	Trump accused Congress of overreach on the legislation, which "handcuffs" him from easing Russia penalties.
en_167468_3	Moscow said the sanctions "put paid to hopes that our relations with the new American administration" would improve.
en_167468_4	Russian Prime Minister Dmitry Medvedev also said this move meant the US had declared a "full-scale trade war" on Russia.
